        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>7th Sep 23 Elul 5623</date>
            </p>
            <p>The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Many thanks for the<lb/> photographs you so kindly sent me<lb/> in
                your favor of <date>1st</date>. One copy<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs De Sola</persName> will give to <persName>Mrs J A
                Joseph</persName><lb/> as you promised her one—the other<lb/>
                <add>לָעַד בַּסֵּפֶר יוּחַק. בְּרִית עולָם בַּל יֻמְחַק. אֶת אַבְרָהָם וְאֶת
                    יִצְחָק</add><lb/> which means that both my wife<lb/> and myself will be proud
                to preserve<lb/> in our album the lineaments of<lb/> one we so highly esteem, and
                who<lb/> deserves so well of <placeName>Israel</placeName>. I wish<lb/> with the
                    <persName>Payton</persName> I could add the<lb/> scriptural <add>והיה הוא
                    ותמורתו</add>—but I cannot<lb/> have the pleasure of <hi rend="underline"
                    >exchanging</hi></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>for the simple reason that<lb/> I do not possess a photographic<lb/> portrait of
                either myself or my<lb/> better half—besides, I am afraid<lb/> you would find my
                exchange if<lb/> not looking exactly like <persName>Isaac's</persName><lb/> of old,
                yet having something<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">sheepish</hi> about it. As soon as<lb/> I have copies I will
                send them.<lb/> I have just had the inexpressible<lb/> pleasure of receiving home
                a<lb/> capital likeness—more beautifully<lb/> &amp; successfully done—of my
                late<lb/> father <add>ע"ה</add>. It was taken from<lb/> a photograph done some 17
                years<lb/> ago, and is a faithful representation<lb/> of what he was at that
                period.<lb/> The copy just done for me is<lb/> also by a Jewish artist, a
                member<lb/> of my congregation, and is life size.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>This leads me to tell you that I<lb/> have completed the Biography and<lb/> sent the
                M.S. to the family. After<lb/> the Holy days I shall see about its<lb/> publication.
                    <add>א"יה צח</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You have said it. My<lb/> own work deprives me the pleasure<lb/> of
                corresponding with many esteemed<lb/> friends. I may add without flattery<lb/> that
                with no one sooner than<lb/> yourself would I desire frequently,<lb/> to exchange
                thoughts, as I think<lb/> we belong pretty much to the same<lb/> school. But my
                ordinary avocations<lb/> and the education—or rather,<lb/> superintendence of the
                education<lb/> of my children leave me little<lb/> leisure.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Sarah Joseph</persName> has just<lb/> come in and desires
                me to say<lb/> she would not accept the</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>duplicate photograph even if I<lb/> gave it her, as she does not think<lb/> it good,
                but wishes you to send<lb/> her another kind. Another member<lb/> of my congregation
                    <add>?</add> artist who spent<lb/>
                <date>Friday</date> evening with us thinks it<lb/> a capital thing artistically
                speaking,<lb/> Still I also like the one in which you<lb/> are represented sitting
                in a chair<lb/> and would like to obtain a copy if<lb/> procurable.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I shall speak to <persName>Wm<lb/> Benjamin</persName> about his
                father's indebtedness<lb/> and hope to write you again after<lb/>
                <add>כפור</add>. Meanwhile receive my best<lb/> wishes (and my wife's too) for
                your<lb/> well-being</p>
            <p>
                <add>יבו ה' אתך את הברכה בכל מעשיך להכתב ולהחתם</add>
                <lb/>
                <add>לחיים טובים ארוכים ולשלום לכי"ר</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin.">Please hand enclosed to
                    <persName>Miss Gratz</persName>.</p>
        </body>
